al ji came forward and took responsibility of registering our society with the help of his personal CA. In the meeting other member has also spoken to CA. Very soon or before Independence Day we will get registered .\r\n<div class=\"text_exposed_show\">\r\n\r\n2. Ashish Sundriyal ji shared his experience of both the schools where he went to provide help to needy students. He has done incredible job in spite of bad weather conditions in Uttrakhand. Cheers and kudos to Ashish ji. Now we have a new enthusiast Akhilesh Nauriyal ji who volunteered for the next trip which is inspiring and great news for our group.\r\n\r\n3. Suresh Badola JI our one of the old members rejoined us as due to his busy schedule he was not able to attend meeting but now he promised us give his maximum time and shared his experience of forming society his inputs and participation is valuable and will be great help .\r\n\r\n4. Another cheerful news was that 15 members attended the meeting and collection was also quite good .it was in excess of Rs.10,800. We will put bank details soon .\r\n\r\n5. Ashish Lakhera JI has taken PD\'s work on war footing as he is continuously getting donation from non PD members and officially he is trying to list PD IN CSR so that PD will get regular donations from his company . We all can try some sort of this thing .\r\n\r\n6. One more thing was decided that instead of third Sunday the meeting will be held on 2nd or 4th Sunday. We will soon put decision after discussion.\r\n\r\n7. I am happy to announce that two of our members, Ashish Lakhera ji and Ms. Anita Bhat got engaged to each other and happily announced the friendly relation transforming into personal relation ,I am sharing this news as to point out here that our bonding and faith within the PD is getting so strong that we taking our friendly and personal relation on a strong level\r\n\r\n8. Last but not the least I would like to thank all the members who attended the meet in the rainy season and promised th