n isolation. A child will go to school only if the family income is good. Realizing this, Pahadi Dagdya, beginning in the corridors of education, adopted a lifecycle approach of development by providing the child with financial aid so that he or she can come to school.\r\n\r\nThis poverty damages childhood with significant effects on a childs physical and mental health, as well as educational achievement. It limits the expectations of the childs ability to perform well in school,. For this reason, Pahadi Dagdya also identifies and encourages the dropouts to continue their education.\r\n\r\nThe poor and underprivileged kids lag at all stages of education. When earning a livelihood and taking care of the members of the family becomes a primary matter of concern in ones life, education stands a little or, very often, no chance of pursuance. For many underprivileged children education is a high-priced luxury, So, Pahadi dagdya took an initiative for providing assistance to these kids. It has already helped 93 such kids.\r\n\r\nIt believes that unless members of the civil society are involved proactively in the process of development, sustainable change will not happen. Following this model of Civic Driven Change, Pahadi Dagdya sensitizes and engages the civil society by holding valuable meetings wherever and whenever possible on important issues.\r\nIt is also equipped with its own newsletter which can elaborate upon the news related to its latest achievement, ongoing work and future projects. Moreover, Pahadi Dagdya is gathering attention over social platforms as it actively shares the eye catching and important information regarding Uttarakhand and their people which is liked by many.\r\nToday, 8 million children in India are out of school  surrounded by poverty and despair; they are fighting a daily battle for their education. Pahadi Dagdya wants to bring hope in their lives. So lets be together and bring a change and make it last.','We Support Child Education','','inherit','closed','closed','','6-revision-v1','','','2017-05-14 21:36:38','2017-05-14 16:06:38','',6,'http://pahadidagdya.com/?p=1183',0,'revision','',0),(1187,1,'2017-07-21 11:35:56','2017-07-21 06:05:56','We salute our   members who decided to support a Child who was struggling with his health but has a dream to learn English.\r\nShri Tejram Sharma ji and Shri Kuldeep Thapliyal ji on their own visited his Institute and paid his fees from their pocket. Now they have also pledged to support him further. We feel proud of them.\r\n\r\n[ngg_images source=\"galleries\" container_ids=\"57\" sortorder=\"386,384,385,383\" display_type=\"photocrati-nextgen_basic_thumbnails\" override_thumbnail_settings=\"1\" thumbnail_width=\"240\" thumbnail_height=\"180\" thumbnail_crop=\"1\" images_per_page=\"10\" number_of_columns=\"0\" ajax_pagination=\"1\" show_all_in_lightbox=\"0\" use_imagebrowser_effect=\"1\" show_slideshow_link=\"1\" slideshow_link_text=\"Delhi_Student_Jul_2017\" template=\"default\" slug=\"Delhi_Student_Jul_2017\" order_by=\"sortorder\" order_direction=\"ASC\" returns=\"included\" maximum_entity_count=\"500\"]','Helping hands are better than praying lips..','','publish','closed','closed','','helping-hands-are-better-than-praying-lips','','','2017-07-22 07:40:34','2017-07-22 02:10:34','',0,'http://pahadidagdya.com/?p=1187',0,'post','',0),(1188,1,'2017-07-22 07:33:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','eyJpZF9maWVsZCI6IklEIiwiX19kZWZhdWx0c19zZXQiOnRydWV9','Untitled ngg_gallery','','draft','closed','closed','','mixin_nextgen_table_extras','','','2017-07-22 07:33:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','eyJpZF9maWVsZCI6IklEIiwiX19kZWZhdWx0c19zZXQiOnRydWV9',0,'http://pahadidagdya.com/?p=1188',0,'ngg_gallery','',0),(1189,1,'2017-07-22 07:33:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','eyJpZF9maWVsZCI6IklEIiwiX19kZWZhdWx0c19zZXQiOnRydWV9','Untitled ngg_pictures','','draft','closed','closed','','mixin_nextgen_table_extras','','','2017-07-22 07:33:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00','eyJpZF9maWVsZCI6IklEIiwiX19kZWZhdWx0c19zZXQ